      <p class="intro-body">
        People have very different ideas with respect to their definition of stress. Probably the most common is,
        “physical, mental, or emotional strain or tension”. Another popular definition of stress is, “a condition or
        feeling experienced
        when a person perceives that demands exceed the personal and social resources the individual is able to
        mobilize.”</p>
      <h2>If Life Were Easy They Would Have Asked For Volunteers</h2>
